⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Mother Brain
node MET · MET · ⟦Mother Brain:MET:590791⟧

WHO   — Mother Brain — the bio-mechanical ruler
WHAT  — The final boss of both Metroid (1986) and Super Metroid — the brain fused to the machine that commands the Pirate fortress and breeds the Metroid menace in the depths of Tourian.
WHERE — MET · Metroid  Framework inputs: Metroid (1986) & Super Metroid (1994)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because she would turn the Metroids into a weapon to dominate the galaxy; because Zebes is her fortress and her body both; because nothing descends into Tourian and is meant to leave.
HOW   — By the defenses of Zebes wired into her own nervous system, by Rinka turrets and the surrounding glass tank in the original — and in Super Metroid, by rising on a towering mechanical body whose rainbow beam nearly kills Samus.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the will inside the fortress — the brain that the planet obeys, and the last thing the Metroids will ever call mother.

spoken token : deith-mith-phan   ·   hex : 590791
